meanings.definition: Not able to be dated or determined.
meanings.sent1: The ancient artifact was undatable due to the missing inscriptions.
meanings.sent2: The fossil was undatable because of the lack of clear markings.
meanings.sent3: The mystery surrounding the undatable painting intrigued art historians.
meanings.sent4: Her thoughts were undatable, like trying to grasp smoke.
meanings.sent5: The encrypted message was as undatable as a secret code.

meanings.definition: Not suitable or eligible for dating or a romantic relationship.
meanings.sent1: His rude behavior made him undatable to most people.
meanings.sent2: She found his constant lies undatable and decided to end the relationship.
meanings.sent3: The undatable bachelor's attempts at flirting were always awkward.
meanings.sent4: Her heart was undatable, guarded by walls of past hurt.
meanings.sent5: The mismatched personalities made them undatable as a couple.
